articles.description: The Nevada Wolf Pack seems to have finally gotten the hang of being ranked in the Top 25.
articles.headline: No. 24 Nevada plays at Utah State

articles.description: Jalen Hayes scored 24 points and Oakland beat Cleveland State 82-66 on Friday night to give coach Greg Kampe his 600th career victory.
articles.headline: Oakland wins 82-66 for Kampe's 600 victory

articles.description: Isaiah Reese had 26 points and matched a career-high with six steals to lead Canisius to a 78-60 victory over Monmouth on Friday night for its sixth straight win.
articles.headline: Reese scores 26 points, leads Canisius over Monmouth 79-60

articles.description: Seth Towns had seven of his 24 points in the final 3 1/2 minutes, Christian Juzang added a career-high 21 points, and Harvard survived with a 65-58 win over Brown on Friday night.
articles.headline: Harvard beats Brown 65-58, stays tied for first in Ivy

articles.description: Blake Reynolds scored 17 points, Miye Oni added 15 and Yale rolled to a 77-65 victory over Dartmouth on Friday night.
articles.headline: Reynolds, Oni lead Yale over Dartmouth 77-65

articles.description: Matt Mobley scored 26 points and grabbed a key rebound with 4.2 seconds left, and St. Bonaventure beat Rhode Island 77-74 to snap the 16th-ranked Rams' 16-game winning streak on Friday night.
articles.headline: St. Bonaventure upsets No. 16 Rhode Island with 77-74 win

images.caption: Bonnies big man LaDarien Griffin slams home the go-ahead bucket and Rhode Island's Jared Terrell's three is no good as the St. Bonaventure student section storms the court.
images.name: St. Bonaventure knocks off No. 16 Rhode Island in dramatic fashion

videos.description: Payton Willis sends a no-look pass inside to Clevon Brown who throws down a two-handed slam in the first half against Tennessee.
videos.headline: Vanderbilt's Willis finds Brown for the flush

videos.description: Saben Lee drives from the outside corner and rises up for the one-handed slam against Tennessee.
videos.headline: Vanderbilt's Lee hammers home dunk

videos.description: Jordan Bowden knocks in a baseline jumper and draws the foul to give the Volunteers a chance at the extra point.
videos.headline: Bowden creates a 3-point play for Tennessee

videos.description: Lamonte Turner dishes to Admiral Schofield who goes up-and-under for a nice layup to shrink Tennessee's deficit in the second half.
videos.headline: Tennessee's Schofield hangs in the air for basket

videos.description: James Daniel III sends a quick bounce pass to Grant Williams who banks in the layup to give Tennessee a one-point lead in the second half against Vanderbilt
videos.headline: Daniel connects with Williams to put Tennessee ahead

videos.description: Grant Williams spins around Vanderbilt defenders to score a nice basket and draws the foul in the second half.
videos.headline: Tennessee's Williams capitalizes on turnover for bucket and-1

videos.description: Grant Williams comes from behind and rises up to reject Vanderbilt's Payton Willis at the rim in the second half.
videos.headline: Williams takes charge with aggressive block

videos.description: Grant Williams rises above a Vanderbilt defender and hits a tricky jumper to give him a new career-high 34 points against Vanderbilt.
videos.headline: Williams' elevates for basket and new career high

videos.description: After his 37-point performance, Grant Williams talks about preparing for the next big game against Texas A&M.
videos.headline: Williams reflects on new career high against Vanderbilt
